:glacial_setting
    a skos:Concept ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy cs: ;
    skos:definition "A SETTING in which geomorphic UNITS are primarily formed by glacial, periglacial and proglacial processes on modern or previously glaciated coasts or on the CONTINENTAL SHELF (PHYSIOGRAPHY)."@en ;
    skos:historyNote "2026-05: This Concept was updated in 2026 following revision and maintenance of the ISGM 2-part geomorphic classification scheme." ;
